Xenophagy
The selective degradation of microorganisms (such as bacteria, fungi, parasites or viruses) through an autophagyrelated mechanism.

Macroautophagy
(Also known as autophagy). The largely non-specific autophagic sequestration of cytoplasm into a doubleor multiple-membranedelimited compartment (an autophagosome) of nonlysosomal origin. Note that certain proteins, organelles and pathogens may be selectively degraded via macroautophagy.

