Microautophagy
The uptake and degradation of cytoplasm by invagination of the lysosomal membrane.

Chaperone-mediated autophagy
The import and degradation of soluble cytosolic proteins by chaperone-dependent, direct translocation across the lysosomal membrane.

Small interfering RNA
(siRNA). Synthetic RNA molecules of 19–23 nucleotides that are used to ‘knockdown’ (that is, silence the expression of) a specific gene. This is known as RNA interference (RNAi) and is mediated by the sequencespecific degradation of mRNA.

